      • initialize

        public void initialize(URL url,
                       ResourceBundle rb)
        Initializes the controller class that adds all the needed functionality, to the: ServiceMatchingView.FXML view. The following setups will be started: - Set the back button - Set the title of the view - Make a instance - Setup a refresh timer and start this - Make a Lost and Found data object - Initialize the different tables - Set the tables with the right data - Stop the tables from being moved //Reset manual matching - Set the on matching view to true
        Specified by:
        initialize in interface javafx.fxml.Initializable
        Parameters:
        url - location used to resolve relative paths for the root object
        rb - resources used to localize the root object

      • addToManualMatching

        public int addToManualMatching(javafx.scene.layout.Pane paneType,
                               int tab,
                               int idCheck,
                               int idObj,
                               String idDataObj,
                               String viewLink)
        Methode for setting the right data in the right place for: MANUAL MATCHING -(Checks used for not resetting the views)
        Parameters:
        paneType - = id of pane were the view needs to be loaden
        tab - = tab that needs to be setted.
        idCheck - = standard value that in the loop gets checked & returned
        idObj - = id thats been set (from id) in the loop for checking
        idDataObj= - String id of the added luggage -> used for checking
        viewLink - = link of fxml that needs to be set in the @paneType
        Returns:
        idCheck to stop the loop from going to far
